          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> be an object in a category <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> such that all binary cartesian products with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> exist. We say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em>exponentiable</fr:em> when the product endofunctor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[-\times  E]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> has a right adjoint, which we shall write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E\Rightarrow -]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
